CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 3 reads: "Survived Crash - Alidis Jones (center) of 608 Regis Way, East Liberty, whose car was hit head on by the station wagon which brought a fiery death to three men, together ...(left to right) Benjamin Norris and Frederick Barker, passengers in Jones' car, are shown shortly after telling Sarah Fields and Martha Jane Walker (right) of the accident. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Car accident survivors Benjamin Norris, Alidis Jones, and Frederick Barker, seated with Sarah Fields and Martha Jane Walker in living room of 608 Regis Way, another version
